<br>
as customers, asking for the bugs to be fixed is the wrong thing; it is the failure in the systematic process (or lack thereof) which permitted bugs to reach the live server that should be examined.<br>
<br>
by asking simply for bugfixes, we are setting ourselves up for more bugs in the future.  i, for one, would rather avoid such short-sightedness.<br>
<br>
i would rather ask scott specifically what changes have been made (not 'are being made' or 'could be made') to the QA process that will keep bugs similar to all those found in the most recent patch from reaching us again.<br>
<br>
getting a bug fixed is not a victory; by then it has already been inflicted upon us.  it's only a consolation.<br>
<br>
<br>
