<br>
No, it's called &quot;time management&quot; and &quot;pick your battles&quot;.<br>
<br>
They aren't here to get involved in flame wars or debates where one paladin can't agree with another paladin. In general, they'll read a lot and use ideas that they like or think will be helpful.<br>
<br>
Ie., they'll read a lot and say a little.<br>
<br>
Only reason Scott posted was because we demanded an answer, and because he felt he should post it. He could have noted the problem, fixed it, and had Absor mention it in the next patch (assuming Absor remembered <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ), but that's bad CS. Good CS is to say &quot;It's being fixed now&quot;, and fix it.<br>
<br>
I can guarantee you they've seen our posts on the balancing forum. How much credence they give it, in the scheme of things, I don't know. At the same point, from having talked to Scott in person at the Boston Fan Faire (hi Scott, I'm the one who thanked you about the healing penalty and asked about bow skill caps), they're reworking a lot of the game and trying to rebalance it at the same time. Scott and his crew are a very busy bunch of folks.<br>
<br>
Keep in mind that the team working on EQ now is mostly a new crew. They're going in and fixing a lot of the very broken shit that has caused problem after problem in the system for so long. They're trying to fix things one thing at a time while trying to break as little else in the process. Bad things will happen; the alternative is to deal with the system exactly as it stands right now. I don't consider that acceptable, and from the impression I got when I talked to him, neither do they.<br>
<br>
Scott's opinions, insofar as I was able to determine what they were, show a lot of rational thinking and reflect a lot of what players have said all along-- not &quot;The Vision&quot;. Exactly how much that impacts the game remains to be seen, but honestly, he's a guy I respect and trust. A lot more so than Abashi or Absor.<br>
<br>
